		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.22]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Practice points.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you're going to start a trade skill, save some of up for those.  You can only use PP for trade skills until about level 20, and from that point on it's practice practice practice only.<br><br>I don't think you need to use your points early one for anything other than buying new skills as the come along.  All you combat skills will start maxing out for your level starting around level 5, so there's no great need to be putting PP into them.  As a monk who didn't start using weapons until late in his life, let me advise you to start practicing 1hb and 2hb before level 10.  It will really pay off later.  I didn't start using 1hb until level 20, and it was very hard to be effective with a combat skill in the 20s when near everything else was maxed out close to 100.  <br><br>I'd also recommend saving all your PPs from 20 until 25, when you get dragon punch, and put ALL of them into it.  Short of a weapon, dragon punch will be your heaviest attack, and you'll want it at 50 rather than 25 to start.  Do the same for flying kick at 30.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Alerithon Tigerspirit<br>29 rank monk, E'Ci<br>Avatara</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=9789209967882&num=4&post=1&mid=9789209967882>